CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 4, 1944, pg. 11 reads: "Mrs. F.D.R. Receives Pittsburghers - During a six-hour stay in Pittsburgh last Friday. Mrs. Franklin D. Roosevelt met and shook hands with nearly 1,300 Pittsburgh women, in a reception sponsored by the YWCA of the city. in receiving line are Mrs. Roosevelt, Mrs. Robert D. Campbell, president of the YWCA in Pittsburgh; Mrs. L.A. Bellinger of the Centre Avenue branch, prominent AKA soror, and Mrs. Charles R. Miller, Jr.-Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: First Lady Eleanor Roosevelt shaking hands with woman, and president of Pittsburgh YMCA Mrs. Robert D. Campbell standing far right, in interior with ferns and American flag
